{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 15''' is the 15th day of the month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Genkō|ja|元弘|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year / {{ill|Shōkyō|ja|正暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1333]] {{ill|June 27|ja|6月27日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the 【Bunbae River Battle (分倍河原の戦い)】 (– approximately until {{ill|May 16 (old lunar calendar)|ja|5月16日 (旧暦)|lt=5月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}), forces under the command of [[Ashikaga Takauji|足利尊氏]] (who later turned to overthrow the bakufu) secured victory. * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1841]] {{ill|July 3|ja|7月3日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – In the 【Tenpō Reforms (天保の改革)】: Shōgun {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyoshi|ja|徳川家慶|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} approved reforms modeled on those of the 【Kyōhō Reforms (享保の改革)】 and 【Kansei Reforms (寛政の改革)}, ordering strict discipline and a ban on extravagance, enforced by the senior councilor {{ill|Mizuno Tadakuni|ja|水野忠邦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1861]] {{ill|June 22|ja|6月22日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The British H. W. Hansard published Japan’s first English-language newspaper, “The Nagasaki Shippinglist and Advertiser,” in Nagasaki. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1868]] {{ill|July 4|ja|7月4日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the Boshin War (戊辰戦争), hostilities occurred at Ueno (【Ueno Sensō|上野戦争】): defenders in Ueno, holed up at {{ill|Kan'ei-ji|ja|寛永寺|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, were overwhelmed by the imperial forces, leading to the new government’s takeover of Edo. == Births == * {{ill|Kenchō|ja|建暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1251]] {{ill|June 5|ja|6月5日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Tokimune|ja|北条時宗|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 8th regent ({{ill|Shikken|ja|執権|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) of the Kamakura shogunate (died [[1284]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1839]] {{ill|June 25|ja|6月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shimazu Genzō (1st generation)|ja|島津源蔵 (初代)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a businessperson and founder of {{ill|Shimazu Corporation|ja|島津製作所|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (died [[1894]]). * {{ill|Kaei|ja|嘉永|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1850]] {{ill|June 24|ja|6月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Baba Tatsuchō|ja|馬場辰猪|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a political thinker (died [[1888]]). == Deaths == * {{ill|Genna|ja|元和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1615]] {{ill|June 11|ja|6月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Sanada Nobushige|ja|真田信繁|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, also known as Yukimura, a military commander (born [[1567]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1842]] {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Suzuki Makino|ja|鈴木牧之|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a merchant and essayist (born [[1770]]).
