== Events == * [[:en:Genkō (1331–1334)|Genkō]] 3rd year / [[:en:Shōryaku|Shōkyō]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1333|1333]] [[:en:June 27|June 27]]) – In the 【Bunbae River Battle (分倍河原の戦い)】 (– approximately until {{ill|May 16 (Lunisolar)|lt=May 16 (Lunisolar)|lt=May 16 (old lunar calendar)|ja|5月16日 (旧暦)|lt=5月16日|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 16 (old lunar calendar)|qq=}}), forces under the command of [[Ashikaga Takauji|足利尊氏]] (who later turned to overthrow the bakufu) secured victory. * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1841]] [[:en:July 3|July 3]]) – In the 【Tenpō Reforms (天保の改革)】: Shōgun [[:en:Tokugawa Ieyoshi|Tokugawa Ieyoshi]] approved reforms modeled on those of the 【Kyōhō Reforms (享保の改革)】 and 【Kansei Reforms (寛政の改革)}, ordering strict discipline and a ban on extravagance, enforced by the senior councilor [[:en:Mizuno Tadakuni|Mizuno Tadakuni]]. * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1861]] [[:en:June 22|June 22]]) – The British H. W. Hansard published Japan’s first English-language newspaper, “The Nagasaki Shippinglist and Advertiser,” in Nagasaki. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年}}[[Category:Years needing redirect replacements]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1868]] [[:en:July 4|July 4]]) – During the Boshin War (戊辰戦争), hostilities occurred at Ueno (【Ueno Sensō|上野戦争】): defenders in Ueno, holed up at [[:en:Kan'ei-ji|Kan'ei-ji]], were overwhelmed by the imperial forces, leading to the new government’s takeover of Edo. == Births == * [[:en:Kenryaku|Kenchō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1251|1251]] [[:en:June 5|June 5]]) – [[:en:Hōjō Tokimune|Hōjō Tokimune]], the 8th regent ([[:en:Shikken|Shikken]]) of the Kamakura shogunate (died [[:en:1284|1284]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 10th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1839]] [[:en:June 25|June 25]]) – {{ill|Shimazu Genzō (1st generation)|ja|島津源蔵 (初代)|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimazu Genzō (1st generation)|qq=}}, a businessperson and founder of [[:en:Shimadzu|Shimazu Corporation]] (died [[1894]]). * [[:en:Kaei|Kaei]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1850]] [[:en:June 24|June 24]]) – [[:en:Baba Tatsui|Baba Tatsuchō]], a political thinker (died [[1888]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Yuanhe|Genna]] 1st year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1615|1615]] [[:en:June 11|June 11]]) – [[:en:Sanada Yukimura|Sanada Nobushige]], also known as Yukimura, a military commander (born [[:en:1567|1567]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 13rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1842]] [[:en:June 23|June 23]]) – {{ill|Suzuki Makino|ja|鈴木牧之|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzuki Makino|qq=}}, a merchant and essayist (born [[1770]]).
