== Events == * {{ill|Genkō (1331–1334)|en|Genkō (1331–1334)|qid=Q1194556|lt=Genkō|1=Genkō (1331–1334)}} 3rd year / {{ill|Shōryaku|en|Shōryaku|qid=Q1324858|lt=Shōkyō|1=Shōryaku}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1333|en|1333|qid=Q6004|lt=1333|1=1333}} {{ill|June 27|en|June 27|qid=Q2664|lt=June 27|1=June 27}}) – In the 【Bunbae River Battle (分倍河原の戦い)】 (– approximately until {{ill|May 16 (Lunisolar)|lt=May 16 (Lunisolar)|lt=May 16 (old lunar calendar)|ja|5月16日 (旧暦)|lt=5月16日|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/May 16 (old lunar calendar)|qq=}}), forces under the command of {{ill|Ashikaga Takauji|en|Ashikaga Takauji|qid=Q297107|lt=足利尊氏|1=Ashikaga Takauji}} (who later turned to overthrow the bakufu) secured victory. * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1841|en|1841|qid=Q7622|lt=1841|1=1841}} {{ill|July 3|en|July 3|qid=Q2699|lt=July 3|1=July 3}}) – In the 【Tenpō Reforms (天保の改革)】: Shōgun {{ill|Tokugawa Ieyoshi|en|Tokugawa Ieyoshi|qid=Q439675|lt=Tokugawa Ieyoshi|1=Tokugawa Ieyoshi}} approved reforms modeled on those of the 【Kyōhō Reforms (享保の改革)】 and 【Kansei Reforms (寛政の改革)}, ordering strict discipline and a ban on extravagance, enforced by the senior councilor {{ill|Mizuno Tadakuni|en|Mizuno Tadakuni|qid=Q2975848|lt=Mizuno Tadakuni|1=Mizuno Tadakuni}}. * {{ill|Bunkyū|en|Bunkyū|qid=Q730266|lt=Bunkyū|1=Bunkyū}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1861|en|1861|qid=Q7693|lt=1861|1=1861}} {{ill|June 22|en|June 22|qid=Q2663|lt=June 22|1=June 22}}) – The British H. W. Hansard published Japan’s first English-language newspaper, “The Nagasaki Shippinglist and Advertiser,” in Nagasaki. * {{ill|Meiji Gannen|ja|明治元年|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji Gannen|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 1868年|1=1868|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q7717}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1868|en|1868|qid=Q7717|lt=1868|1=1868}} {{ill|July 4|en|July 4|qid=Q2698|lt=July 4|1=July 4}}) – During the Boshin War (戊辰戦争), hostilities occurred at Ueno (【Ueno Sensō|上野戦争】): defenders in Ueno, holed up at {{ill|Kan'ei-ji|en|Kan'ei-ji|qid=Q3120766|lt=Kan'ei-ji|1=Kan'ei-ji}}, were overwhelmed by the imperial forces, leading to the new government’s takeover of Edo. == Births == * {{ill|Kenryaku|en|Kenryaku|qid=Q1194260|lt=Kenchō|1=Kenryaku}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1251|en|1251|qid=Q5494|lt=1251|1=1251}} {{ill|June 5|en|June 5|qid=Q2622|lt=June 5|1=June 5}}) – {{ill|Hōjō Tokimune|en|Hōjō Tokimune|qid=Q430964|lt=Hōjō Tokimune|1=Hōjō Tokimune}}, the 8th regent ({{ill|Shikken|en|Shikken|qid=Q1045904|lt=Shikken|1=Shikken}}) of the Kamakura shogunate (died {{ill|1284|en|1284|qid=Q5544|lt=1284|1=1284}}). * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 10th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1839|en|1839|qid=Q7616|lt=1839|1=1839}} {{ill|June 25|en|June 25|qid=Q2662|lt=June 25|1=June 25}}) – {{ill|Shimazu Genzō (1st generation)|ja|島津源蔵 (初代)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shimazu Genzō (1st generation)|1=Genzō Shimazu I|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11476816}}, a businessperson and founder of {{ill|Shimadzu|en|Shimadzu|qid=Q517117|lt=Shimazu Corporation|1=Shimadzu}} (died {{ill|1894|en|1894|qid=Q7843|lt=1894|1=1894}}). * {{ill|Kaei|en|Kaei|qid=Q1146125|lt=Kaei|1=Kaei}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1850|en|1850|qid=Q7653|lt=1850|1=1850}} {{ill|June 24|en|June 24|qid=Q2665|lt=June 24|1=June 24}}) – {{ill|Baba Tatsui|en|Baba Tatsui|qid=Q11667928|lt=Baba Tatsuchō|1=Baba Tatsui}}, a political thinker (died {{ill|1888|en|1888|qid=Q7829|lt=1888|1=1888}}). == Deaths == * {{ill|Yuanhe|en|Yuanhe|qid=Q10889567|lt=Genna|1=Yuanhe}} 1st year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1615|en|1615|qid=Q6784|lt=1615|1=1615}} {{ill|June 11|en|June 11|qid=Q2617|lt=June 11|1=June 11}}) – {{ill|Sanada Yukimura|en|Sanada Yukimura|qid=Q3948081|lt=Sanada Nobushige|1=Sanada Yukimura}}, also known as Yukimura, a military commander (born {{ill|1567|en|1567|qid=Q6642|lt=1567|1=1567}}). * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 13rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1842|en|1842|qid=Q7625|lt=1842|1=1842}} {{ill|June 23|en|June 23|qid=Q2668|lt=June 23|1=June 23}}) – {{ill|Suzuki Makino|ja|鈴木牧之|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzuki Makino|1=Suzuki Bokushi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11649058}}, a merchant and essayist (born {{ill|1770|en|1770|qid=Q7683|lt=1770|1=1770}}).
